    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> (if required!)</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong>,<strong> lemongrass & lime leaf paste</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a large pan, stir in 500ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[750ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [1L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat - this is your <strong>poaching liquid</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-poached-basa-and-tom-kha-rice-with-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 160ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-poached-basa-and-tom-kha-rice-with-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel your <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate)</p><p>Add the ginger to the <strong>poaching liquid</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-poached-basa-and-tom-kha-rice-with-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut each <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> into 3 equal portions and season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Pick the <strong>leaves</strong> off your <strong>coriander</strong> stalks and set them aside for garnish</p><p>Chop the <strong>stems</strong> finely and add them to the <strong>poaching liquid</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-poached-basa-and-tom-kha-rice-with-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Carefully add each piece of <strong>fish</strong> to the pan of <strong>poaching liquid</strong>, trying not to overlap them</p><p>Cook for 8 min, carefully turning the fish halfway through for even cooking</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-poached-basa-and-tom-kha-rice-with-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice your <strong>white cup mushrooms</strong> finely</p><p>Add the <strong>mushrooms</strong> and your <strong>fish sauce</strong> to the pan</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-poached-basa-and-tom-kha-rice-with-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, transfer the <strong>poached fish</strong> to a plate</p><p>Add the cooked <strong>rice</strong> to the<strong> poaching liquid </strong>and<strong> </strong>stir to combine - this is your <strong>tom kha cauliflower rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-poached-basa-and-tom-kha-rice-with-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Divide the<strong> tom kha cauliflower rice</strong> between your bowls and top with the <strong>poached fish</strong></p><p>Garnish with the coriander leaves</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
